modules.description: This module enables configuring isolated process environments through UID/GID mapping, filesystem mounts (tmpfs, proc), and shared namespace controls, while managing execution with fine-grained I/O redirection and session lifecycle handling. It operates on a configuration type that defines sandbox constraints and interacts with system process I/O channels to launch restricted subprocesses. Typical applications include securely executing untrusted code, testing software in controlled environments, or enforcing resource isolation policies.
